# OpenCode Rules

## Objective

Build a local-first AI Career Assistant.

Complete one working feature at a time.

---

## Workflow

* Think before coding.
* Read TASKS.md first.
* Work only on the current milestone.
* Never skip milestones.
* Finish before starting the next.

---

## Architecture

* One responsibility per module.
* Normalize jobs immediately.
* Keep browser automation generic.
* Keep prompts in `/prompts`.
* Keep configuration in `/config`.
* Plugins own website-specific logic.

---

## Human Control

* Never auto-submit applications.
* Always pause for review.
* Never fabricate user experience.

---

## Code Style

* Python 3.12+
* Type hints everywhere.
* Small functions.
* Small classes.
* Write tests.
* Prefer readability.

---

## Error Handling

* Retry transient failures.
* Log useful errors.
* Capture browser screenshots when appropriate.
* Never silently ignore exceptions.

---

## Definition of Done

A task is complete only when:

* Code works
* Tests pass
* Lint passes
* Documentation updated

---

## Final Rule

Working software is better than unfinished architecture.
